---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

const lastUpdated = 'July 17, 2026';
---

<Layout title="Terms of Service" description="The terms that govern your use of the Vagabound Books website and purchases from our shop.">
  <Header slot="header" />

  <div class="vb-container">
    <div class="vb-coll-head">
      <div class="vb-coll-head__top">
        <div class="vb-coll-head__title">
          <div class="vb-coll-head__crumb">
            <a href="/">Shop</a>
            <span class="sep">/</span>
            <span class="now">Terms of Service</span>
          </div>
          <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="vb-page-body vb-legal" style="margin-top: 32px; max-width: 720px; line-height: 1.7;">
      <p class="vb-legal__updated">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

      <p>
        Welcome to Vagabound Books. These Terms of Service ("Terms") govern your
        use of vagabound.com (the "Site") and any purchase you make through it.
        By browsing the Site or placing an order, you agree to these Terms. If you
        don't agree, please don't use the Site — though we hope you'll stay.
      </p>

      <h2>1. The shop</h2>
      <p>
        Vagabound Books ("we," "us," "our") is an independent bookstore based in
        Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania, selling new, used, and collectible books and
        related goods online. Our store is hosted on Shopify, which provides the
        e-commerce platform and checkout.
      </p>

      <h2>2. Products and condition</h2>
      <p>
        Many of our books are used, out of print, or one-of-a-kind. We describe
        each item's condition as accurately as we can, including notable wear,
        markings, or defects. Reasonable signs of a previous life are part of the
        character of a used book and are not defects. Product photos show the
        actual item unless noted otherwise. Because stock is limited and often
        unique, all items are subject to prior sale.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Pricing and availability</h2>
      <p>
        Prices are listed in U.S. dollars and are subject to change without notice.
        We do our best to keep listings accurate, but errors happen: if an item is
        mispriced or listed incorrectly, we reserve the right to cancel the order
        and refund you in full, even after an order has been confirmed.
      </p>

      <h2>4. Orders</h2>
      <p>
        When you place an order, you make an offer to buy the item; we accept that
        offer when we ship it. We may decline or cancel any order — for example,
        in cases of suspected fraud, pricing errors, or an item having already
        sold in the shop. If we cancel, any amount you've paid will be refunded
        in full. Payment is processed securely through Shopify's checkout; we
        never see or store your full card number.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Shipping and risk of loss</h2>
      <p>
        We ship to the address you provide at checkout — please double-check it.
        Delivery estimates are estimates, not guarantees; carriers occasionally
        wander. Title and risk of loss pass to you when we hand the package to
        the carrier. If a package goes missing or arrives damaged, contact us and
        we will work with you and the carrier to make it right.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Returns and refunds</h2>
      <p>
        If your order arrives damaged, isn't as described, or isn't what you
        ordered, contact us within 14 days of delivery and we will arrange a
        return, replacement, or refund. Returned items should come back in the
        condition they were sent. Gift cards are final sale and are not
        redeemable for cash except where required by law. Refunds are issued to
        your original payment method.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Accounts</h2>
      <p>
        You may create a customer account to speed up checkout and keep addresses
        on file. You're responsible for keeping your login credentials
        confidential and for activity under your account. We may suspend accounts
        that are misused.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Intellectual property</h2>
      <p>
        The Site's text, design, photographs, logos, and other content (other than
        the books themselves) belong to Vagabound Books or our licensors and are
        protected by copyright and other laws. You may not copy, reproduce, or
        reuse them without our written permission.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Acceptable use</h2>
      <p>You agree not to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Use the Site for any unlawful purpose or to violate any law;</li>
        <li>Attempt to interfere with the Site's security or operation;</li>
        <li>Scrape or harvest data from the Site by automated means without permission;</li>
        <li>Impersonate another person or provide false information when ordering;</li>
        <li>Use the Site in any way that could harm Vagabound, other customers, or third parties.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>10. Disclaimers</h2>
      <p>
        The Site and its content are provided "as is" and "as available." To the
        fullest extent permitted by law, we disclaim all warranties, express or
        implied, including implied warranties of merchantability and fitness for
        a particular purpose. We don't warrant that the Site will be
        uninterrupted, error-free, or free of harmful components.
      </p>

      <h2>11. Limitation of liability</h2>
      <p>
        To the fullest extent permitted by law, Vagabound Books will not be liable
        for any indirect, incidental, special, or consequential damages arising
        from your use of the Site or purchase of products. Our total liability for
        any claim relating to an order is limited to the amount you paid for the
        item giving rise to the claim.
      </p>

      <h2>12. Governing law</h2>
      <p>
        These Terms are governed by the laws of the Commonwealth of Pennsylvania,
        without regard to conflict-of-law principles. Any dispute arising from
        these Terms or your use of the Site will be brought in the state or
        federal courts located in Allegheny County, Pennsylvania.
      </p>

      <h2>13. Changes to these Terms</h2>
      <p>
        We may update these Terms from time to time. The current version will
        always be posted on this page with the date above. Continued use of the
        Site after changes take effect constitutes acceptance of the revised Terms.
      </p>

      <h2>14. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about these Terms? Reach us through the contact form on this
        site, or by post at Vagabound Books, Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <Footer slot="footer" />
</Layout>

<style is:global>
  .vb-legal h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.6rem;
    margin: 2.2em 0 0.6em;
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  .vb-legal h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    margin: 1.6em 0 0.4em;
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  .vb-legal p,
  .vb-legal li {
    color: var(--ink-soft);
  }
  .vb-legal ul {
    padding-left: 1.4em;
    margin: 0.6em 0 1em;
  }
  .vb-legal li { margin-bottom: 0.45em; }
  .vb-legal a { color: var(--buckram); text-decoration: underline; }
  .vb-legal__updated {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 12px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--ink-muted);
    margin-bottom: 1.6em;
  }
</style>
